I"b<p>Considering that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/version-control-systems-empower-creatives">version control systems</a> can be used to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/archiving-persists-knowledge-work">persist knowledge</a>, it’s easy to see how they can be used in the context of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-has-a-cognitive-architecture">the second brain architecture</a>. Besides simply recording past changes of evergreen notes, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/version-control-systems-empower-creatives">version control systems</a> enable the creation snapshots of the user’s past <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conversational-interfaces-render-knowledge-bases-into-agents">selves</a>. Over time, snapshots can significantly diverge in ways of thinking and style of speech.</p>
